367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.097e7dbd-b941-4682-b5c6-a574dc984424.prompt=Enter a value for proxyPassword 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.1d676ea1-98a9-43b4-b59b-6c978d186b5b.prompt=Enter a value for keystorePassword 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.2b8c3efd-e964-4f02-8739-5f08354f4155.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.2d438be6-097b-4106-9645-fd16cbf5287f.prompt=Enter a value for encodeURL 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.32e57cc3-0190-4d91-9d52-e29716e20289.description=
Filters XML based on provided criteria. If 'path' is specified, searches XML for all paths that match the specified 'path'. Paths can be specified from the root element or as an arbitrary path. Elements can be further filtered based on one of the following criteria. You can filter based on the existence of a specified child element or that child having a specific value. Similarly you can also filter based on the existence of a specified attribute or that attribute having a specified value. You can however only filter based on either a child element or an attribute. For complex filtering, please use the XPath Evaluator operation. 

NOTE\: XML using default namespace is not supported by this operation.

Inputs\:
xml - The XML (in the form of a String).
path - The path to the element (Optional; returns all children if empty).
isPathFromRoot - Is the 'path' specified from root (Defaults to false)?
childName - Additionally, filter based on the existence of a child element named 'childName' (Optional; does not filter based on 'childName' if empty).
childValue - Additionally, filter based on the given 'childName' having this value (Optional; does not filter based on 'childValue' if empty).
attributeName - Additionally, filter based on an attribute with the given 'attributeName' existing (Optional; does not filter based on 'attributeName' if empty).
attributeValue - Additionally, filter based on the given 'attributeName' having this value (Optional; does not filter based on 'attributeValue' if empty).

Responses\:
has more - Another Element was found, and has been returned.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - No more Elements. This will only be returned once, then iteration restarts.

Returns\:
returnResult - The filtered elements.
367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.3d02588f-7c28-4b5a-99ff-a1191e5eae32.prompt=Enter a value for timeout 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.44a98fea-1d69-4c73-9885-bc66853e7024.prompt=Enter a value for userAgent 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.45bb3e13-e3cd-45ee-ac4d-f0b60cd2a978.prompt=Resource Binding ID 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.51dbcba3-d6c3-4d01-8215-1c5f7e70e949.prompt=Enter a value for keystore 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.551ceb42-506f-41cc-b414-445c80afc932.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.5f0310d0-c90c-4c5c-9436-884e289a0f25.prompt=Enter a value for followRedirects 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.6e47d47a-5a31-41f6-9f7c-28cebfbb7714.prompt=Enter a value for trustPassword 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.7716f53b-357a-4281-8b75-bce13d07c22c.description=
Takes a reference to XML (in the form of a String) and the specified XPath Query is run against the XML and returns the results in a form of a delimited list. The World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) organization provides the XPath specification (http\://www.w3.org).

Inputs\:
xml - The XML (in the form of a String)

xpathQuery - The XPath Query that is wanted to be run. See Examples in Notes section below.

delimiter- The delimiter used to separate values in the returnResult list. 

Default value\: ,

Result Value\:
returnResult - The result of the operation. If multiple XPaths are defined then this will add the delimiter between each value. There is no final delimiter.

Notes\:
Examples\:
The XPath Query can be specified as a single query in a format similiar to the following\:
/employees/employee[@id\="3"]/*[name()\="name" or name()\="jobDescription" or name()\="salary" or name()\="managerId"]/text()

This would return the following results\:
Goofy,tester,$50,1

Or if more then one XPath query needs to be specified, populate xpathQuery using the XPath concat function.  As an example here is sample of a xpathQuery value using XPath concat function\:
concat(/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/name/text(),',',/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/jobDescription/text(),',',/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/managerId/text(),',',/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/salary/text())

The output using the concat xpathQuery input would return the following results\:
Donald Duck,Lead Coder,1,$50

The examples above use the following xml string value\:


  
    Mickey Mouse
    Chief
    $100
    
  
  
    Donald Duck
    Lead Coder
    $50
    1
  
  
    Goofy
    tester
    $50
    1
  
  
    Pluto
    Coder - grade 1
    $25
    2
367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.79c947dd-c9b8-46ea-89c0-4853927ab66e.prompt=Enter a value for proxy 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.9e407ab3-02c9-404e-aead-1cadfc342ea5.description=
This workflow returns the details of the given artifact id.

Inputs-
artifactId –   Artifact  Id
userIdentifier  - User Identifier id
authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.

Outputs-
name –  name of the artifactr 
displayName – display name of the artifact
artifactType – Artifact type
state – state of the artifact
lifeCycleState –  life cycle state of the artifact
lifeCycleSubState – life cycle sub state of the artifact
document  – returned XML document from API
367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.a1e297c5-7aa9-4c1c-a504-b850787e6ae2.prompt=Enter a value for proxyPort 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.c6f7332f-ffd7-48b5-bf0a-d3605b0a0bf5.prompt=Enter a value for useCookies 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.cf686aec-2627-4328-ac71-3d96eb1a338c.prompt=Enter a value for sublist 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.description=
Selects providers based on property configured on the provider

Inputs Parameters\:

resourceBindingId - Resource binding ID to update the valid providers
propertyValue - Value of the property based on which the provider should be selected
propertyName - Name of the property based on which the provider should be selected
userIdentifier - userIdentifier for used in REST API calls

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.e0e8ba2f-226f-4dcf-95c6-eae6b72e0d2a.prompt=Enter a value for trustAllRoots 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.e1bf789e-d56d-4e21-af37-870892f2e124.prompt=Enter a value for trustKeystore 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.e1dee384-bd2b-464d-9e4d-d0702826ffda.prompt=Enter a value for authType 367407ba-1fab-4403-ae5a-19cae05fe189.e65c3ff4-048d-4a12-8254-60d2ee963f3d.description=
Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list.

Inputs\:
sublist -The contained list.
container - The containing list.
delimiter - A delimiter separating elements in the two lists. Default is a comma
ignoreCase - If set to 'True' then the compare is not case sensitive. Default is True

Responses\:
true - sublist is contained in container.
false - sublist is not contained in container.

Results\:
Result - All items contained in the sublist that are not in the container.
